TITLE: 'I almost died': PA Senate nominee John Fetterman says he is still recovering from stroke
SUMMARY: Fetterman will compete in the general against either Trump-backed celebrity physician Dr. Mehmet Oz or former hedge fund manager Dave McCormick.

TITLE: Former New York cop arrested outside U.S. Capitol with fake badge, BB gun, body armor, ammo and high-capacity magazines
SUMMARY: Jerome Felipe, a former New York police officer, was spotted parked outside the U.S. Capitol in Washington. He claimed to be an Interpol investigator.

TITLE: 'Lots of luck on his trip to the moon': Biden shrugs off Elon Musk's economic fears, touts Ford investments
SUMMARY: The president had been asked about Musk after a speech in Delaware touting the solid jobs report released earlier Friday.

TITLE: Former Trump aide Peter Navarro indicted for contempt of Congress in defying Jan. 6 Capitol probe subpoena
SUMMARY: Peter Navarro, who served as a trade advisor to former President Donald Trump, refused to testify to the House committee investigating the Capitol riot.

TITLE: Social Security fund will be able to pay benefits one year longer than expected, Treasury says
SUMMARY: The Social Security trust fund will be able to pay out benefits for a year longer than prior estimates, the Treasury Department said.

TITLE: Biden will call for tighter gun laws in televised address Thursday night, following Uvalde and Tulsa massacres
SUMMARY: The use of AR-15-style rifles in recent high-profile mass shootings in the U.S. have spurred renewed calls on Congress to pass gun restriction legislation.

TITLE: More than half of Americans say they are 'pro-choice,' the most since 1995, Gallup finds
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court is poised to overturn Roe v. Wade, which established the constitutional right to abortion, a leaked opinion by Justice Samuel Alito suggests.

TITLE: U.S. goes after more Russian yachts linked to Putin in expanded sanctions
SUMMARY: The Treasury Department expanded sanctions to crack down on Moscow's access to yachts as the U.S. punishes Russian President Vladimir Putin.

TITLE: Angela Merkel breaks silence on Ukraine, calls Russia's war 'barbaric'
SUMMARY: Merkel has come under heavy scrutiny in the last few months for her history of friendly relations with Russian President Vladimir Putin.

TITLE: Here's what's in Biden's $700 million military aid package for Ukraine
SUMMARY: The Biden administration has sent a total of about $4.6 billion to Ukraine since Russia invaded this year, according to the Pentagon.

TITLE: BTS draws massive crowd to White House press briefing ahead of meeting with Biden
SUMMARY: BTS came to the White House to talk to Biden about Asian inclusion and representation, and to discuss a sharp rise in anti-Asian hate crimes in recent years.

TITLE: House Democrats look to pass gun control legislation by early June
SUMMARY: House Democrats will try to advance a raft of gun control bills on Thursday in the wake of two mass shootings that rocked the nation earlier this month.

TITLE: Republicans, Democrats spar over gun regulation after Texas school shooting
SUMMARY: Sen. Chris Murphy said there are "serious" bipartisan negotiations on a new gun law meant to curb future killings.

TITLE: Op-ed: After Davos, going 'long' on optimism in an anxious world
SUMMARY: After Davos, I'm going "short" on pessimism and long on "optimism" as I return to Washington, D.C., this weekend.

TITLE: Judge dismisses Trump federal lawsuit against New York Attorney General Letitia James over her probe of business
SUMMARY: Ex-President Donald Trump and his company are being investigated by New York Attorney General Letitia James over valuations of real estate assets.

TITLE: Rep. Madison Cawthorn discloses 2021 'Let's Go Brandon' cryptocurrency purchase days after ethics probe announced
SUMMARY: Cawthorn bought up to $250,000 worth of "Let's Go Brandon" cryptocurrency a week before suggesting its price would "go to the moon."

TITLE: The National Rifle Association's lobbying machine is still potent despite financial woes that reduced its clout
SUMMARY: The National Rifle Association still has a bevy of assets that it can use to influence the gun policy debate despite financial and internal turmoil.

TITLE: Trump and GOP leaders speak at NRA event in Houston after Texas school shooting
SUMMARY: Trump and Sen. Ted Cruz spoke at the NRA's annual meeting in Houston, just days after a gunman killed 19 children and two adults in a Texas school.

TITLE: Rep. Joaquin Castro asks FBI to investigate police response timeline in Texas school shooting as controversy grows
SUMMARY: The police version of what happened during the shooting at the elementary school in Uvalde, Texas, has changed since Tuesday.

TITLE: Biden to travel to Uvalde to mourn victims of Texas school shooting
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden will travel to Uvalde, Texas on Sunday to grieve with and console the families of the victims of Tuesday's mass shooting.

TITLE: Senate GOP blocks domestic terror bill, as gun reform talks restart after Buffalo, Texas shootings
SUMMARY: Senate Republicans blocked debate on a domestic terrorism bill as the chamber holds talks on separate gun-safety legislation.

TITLE: Trump must answer questions under oath in New York AG probe into business practices, appeals court says
SUMMARY: Ex-President Donald Trump has repeatedly failed to limit the probe by New York Attorney General Letitia James into Trump Organization business practices.

TITLE: Blinken says China is a serious long-term challenge but the U.S. does not want a new Cold War
SUMMARY: Secretary of State Antony Blinken outlined the Biden administration's policy toward China, as the U.S. balances tensions of Russia and Taiwan.

TITLE: National Rifle Association says 'our deepest sympathies' are with families and victims of Uvalde, Texas school massacre
SUMMARY: The NRA, which opposes gun control laws, will host its convention in Texas, days after a lone gunman killed 19 kids and two teachers at Robb Elementary School.

TITLE: ‘Why are we willing to live with this carnage?’ Biden pushes to tighten gun laws after Texas school shooting
SUMMARY: Biden offered condolences and urged lawmakers to resist the gun industry to pass firearm legislation hours after a gunman killed at least 19 children in Texas.

TITLE: Elon Musk backs 'tight' background checks for all gun sales in wake of mass shooting in Texas
SUMMARY: Tesla and SpaceX CEO Elon Musk told CNBC that he believes in tighter background checks for gun owners after the mass shooting in Texas.

TITLE: Pennsylvania announces recount of Senate GOP primary race between Dr. Oz, Dave McCormick
SUMMARY: Oz, who is endorsed by former President Donald Trump, led former hedge funder McCormick in the final tally by less than half a percentage point.

TITLE: CBO boosts U.S. GDP growth estimates, says inflation has topped and will cool to 2% by 2024
SUMMARY: A report released by the Congressional Budget Office on Wednesday estimates that real gross domestic product, or GDP, will advance 3.1% in 2022.

TITLE: Schumer says Democrats want to craft gun reforms with GOP after Texas school massacre
SUMMARY: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer pledged Wednesday to renew efforts to pass stricter U.S. gun-control laws.

TITLE: Trump will speak at NRA event in Houston days after Texas school massacre
SUMMARY: Trump, Texas Gov. Greg Abbott, Sen. Ted Cruz, Gov. Kristi Noem and other GOP politicians are also set to attend the NRA's "Leadership Forum" in Houston.
